  "plainText": "Exclusive to:\nVine\n45 sec\n40\nDropped by\n()\n()\n\"vine\"\n“Maybe I can tie stuff up with this.”\n–Wilson\n“I could use this for something. Or I could just burn it.”\n–Willow\n“For string enemies together.”\n–Wolfgang\n“Unruly life.”\n–Wendy\n“UNRULY NATURE”\n–WX-78\n“A common jungle vine.”\n–Wickerbottom\n“Sigh. Not a tree.”\n–Woodie\n“It's twisted and gnarled.”\n–Maxwell\n“A ropey branch. I can think of nine good uses for it already.”\n–Wagstaff\n“What can yöu dö för me?”\n–Wigfrid\n“This stuff is wild.”\n–Webber\n“Good for lashing stuff down.”\n–Walani\n“Not a single grape on it...”\n–Warly\n“Them's be th'stranglin' kind.”\n–Woodlegs\n“FAST BIND, FAST FIND”\n–Wilba\n“String branches”\n–Wormwood\n“The kind of thing that would be more useful if I had a bunch of them.”\n–Wheeler\nVines are a resource in the Shipwrecked DLC. They are dropped from chopping a Viney Bush with a Machete or by digging one up with a Shovel. Vines are used in several crafting recipes.\nHamlet[edit | edit source]\nVines are also included in the Hamlet DLC, it can be obtained by killing Snaptooth Seedlings, Snaptooth Flytraps and Bramble Blooms. Using a Shears on a Viney Bush will result in 2 Vines instead of the usual one.\nUsage[edit | edit source]\n×3\n×4\n×4\n×3\n×2\n×2\n×4\n×2\n×2\n×3\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×5\n×3\n×6\nView or edit this template\nResources\nAttention: The following categories are only for the players look up the page based on their first impression, they have nothing to do with the actual categories/behavior/function/tags of these items\nPlants\nNatural non-living materials\nMobs Parts\nSkins\nFeathers\nBones and horns\nGems\nShadow Resources\nLunar Resources\nCraftable Resources\nNon-natural materials\nTrinkets\nLost Relics\nTransmission Items",
